                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>“What we learn about space often dramatically changes how we understand ourselves,” Bernhardt wrote. “Now, the potential to discover evidence that we are not the only 'living' planet offers the same opportunity to revise how we understand the universe and our place within it.”</p>
<p>Kruse said as long as NASA’s mission is to explore new worlds, then this is no more than an extension of what humankind has "done forever."</p>
<p>“We’ve explored the Earth, and now we’ve extended our boundaries&mdash;and we want to keep exploring the place we live in, and that is just fine,” he said.</p>
                                    </div>

